-- Tanzania to Decide on BP’s Possible Unit Sale, Citizen Says
-- B y   W i l f r e d   M w a k a l o s i
-- 2010-11-19T06:30:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/tanzania-to-decide-on-bp-s-possible-unit-sale-citizen-newspaper-reports.html
Tanzania will decide whether to
approve the planned sale by BP Plc of its business in the
country when the country’s new cabinet begins operating, the Dar
es Salaam-based Citizen newspaper reported, citing Ramadhani
Kijjah, the permanent secretary in the finance ministry.  The government owns a 50 percent stake in BP’s business in
the country, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wilfred Mwakalosi in Dar es Salaam at 
 wmwakalosi1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  